Describe a goal you set that you tried your best to achieve
- what it was
- why you set this goal
- whether it was difficult to achieve this goal
- explain how you felt about achieving this goal

I’d like to talk about a goal I set for myself, which was learning how to play the guitar.

I was inspired to pursue this goal about two years ago after attending an English club with some friends. While I was there, I saw a girl confidently singing and playing the guitar at the same time. I found it incredibly impressive, and it made me want to be able to do the same.

So, I decided to take it seriously and enrolled in a guitar course. At the beginning, I faced quite a few challenges. I struggled to remember different chords and found it difficult to position my fingers correctly on the strings. On top of that, my fingertips often became sore after practice, which made me feel discouraged at times.

There were moments when I considered giving up, but I managed to stay motivated by imagining myself performing in front of others. I also made a conscious effort to practice more regularly and watched online tutorials to improve my skills.

After about six months of consistent effort, I was finally able to play some of my favorite songs. I felt extremely proud and happy because it was something I had worked very hard to achieve.

Looking back, I’m really glad I didn’t give up. This experience taught me the importance of perseverance and self-discipline, and it showed me that with enough effort, I can achieve my goals.
